# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   For an app, this can be useful so that other developers know which version
#   of Python to use.
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different platforms, you may let Pipfile.lock ignored.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, Poetry uses poetry.lock and pyproject.toml to manage dependencies.
#   You should commit poetry.lock to version control.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv and Poetry, PDM uses pdm.lock to manage dependencies.
#pdm.lock

